Date: Fri 14 Sep 2001 10:57:39 -0300
From: Fernando D.A. Pires <favila@matrix.com.br>
Source: "A Noticia" newspaper, Santa Catarina, Brazil 13 Sep 2001 [in
Portuguese [edited
<http://www.an.com.br>

A 16-year old girl died Tuesday at the Hospital Regional do Oeste in
Chapeco (Santa Catarina) after presenting with high fever, characteristic
yellow appearance & hemorrhage. She had visited Passo Fundo (Rio Grande do
Sul) [the state where monkeys have recently been found dead from YF -- see
refs. above and Palmas (Parana), but the exact dates are not known.
Specimens have been sent to the Instituto Adolfo Lutz, Sao Paulo, Brazil
[for confirmation.
--
Prof. Dr. Fernando Dias de Avila Pires
Instituto Oswaldo Cruz/UFSC
Rua Bico de Lacre, 79
88050-150 Florianopolis, SC, Brazil
